The content of this file is required to run the virtualization platform. 
Here follows a brief explanation of the directories:

bin/
Scripts for starting and stopping the virtualization platform.

sql/
The ddl to any databases that are required to be setup before the
platform can be started

mule-config/
Mule specific configuration that points out the app.home (the location where 
the virtualization platforms configuration is located) as well as the 
directory where virtualized services shall be put 
(default: <vp-home>/vp/services)

vp-config/
Virtualization platform specific configuration files. These must be located in 
<vp-home>/vp/config

Note:   The jmx.password must be read only only to the owner. Do this by:	
		chmod 400 jmx.password or mule won't start properly.
		You can connect to the JVM by using jconsole and enter the
		following remote uri:
		service:jmx:rmi://<host>:1111/jndi/rmi://<host>:1111/jmxrmi

lib/
The libraries that are required to start mule with the virtualization platform. 
These must be put in <mule-home>/lib/user


NOTES
Following services provided when deploying the platform:

https://host:port/vp/GetLogicalAddresseesByServiceContract/1/rivtabp21?wsdl
https://host:port/vp/GetSupportedServiceContracts/1/rivtabp21?wsdl